&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Diabetes Specialist Nurse band 6&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A&lt;/strong&gt; position has arisen for a &lt;strong&gt;Diabetes Specialist Nurse&lt;/strong&gt; to work full time at Frimley Park Hospital.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Within the hospital setting you will be responsible for reviewing in-patients with diabetes, undertaking out-patient clinics and coordinating the treatment plans for patients diagnosed with Diabetes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will also be responsible for running the telephone advice line and email service, and ensuring that written documentation is kept up to date.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You should have current experience as a DSN and be flexible and proactive in your approach. You will be working within the team of DSN&#39;s, ward nurses, practise /community nurses, Diabetologist, GP&#39;s, Dieticians and Podiatrists.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Interview Date: W/C 08/12/20&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Claire Henke]&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title Lead Diabetes Specialist Nurse&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address claire.henke@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 01276 604701&lt;/p&gt;
